msgid "Ring has a webpage dedicated to explaining its privacy pillars and answering frequently asked questions"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "uses_encryption_helptext"
msgid ""
"Videos are encrypted in storage and during transmission. Ring is offering end-to-end encryption. https://blog.ring.com/2020/09/24/ring-announces-end-to-end-encryption-privacy-security-and-user-"
"control-updates/"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "strong_password_helptext"
msgid "Two-factor authentication is now mandatory after major pressure from Mozilla and other groups."
msgstr "La autenticación de dos factores ya es obligatoria tras las presiones llevadas a cabo por Mozilla y otros grupos."

msgctxt "manage_vulnerabilities_helptext"
msgid "Amazon has a <a id=\"a1\">bug bounty program</a>, which means that anyone who finds a security issue and discloses it responsibly may get paid."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "privacy_policy_helptext"
msgid "Ring has a webpage dedicated to explaining it's privacy pillars and answering frequently asked questions"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "tips_to_protect_yourself"
msgid "Turn on <a id=\"a1\">Two-factor Authentication</a>"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "tips_to_protect_yourself"
msgid "<a id=\"a1\">Check</a> if your address is exposed through the Neighbor app"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "tips_to_protect_yourself"
msgid "<a id=\"a1\">Don't share</a> your login-in information"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "tips_to_protect_yourself"
msgid "Review sharing options for your data, if you have multiple people in the neighborhood"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "tips_to_protect_yourself"
msgid "Make sure you are comfortable with the fact that local police may require the footage. Think about all of the personal events cameras inside and outside of your home will capture."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "tips_to_protect_yourself"
msgid "Use strong passwords &amp; unique usernames"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "tips_to_protect_yourself"
msgid "Delete footage as often as you can"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "tips_to_protect_yourself"
msgid "Limit third-party trackers in the Ring app"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "personal_data_collected"
msgid "Name, email, phone number, address"
msgstr "Nombre, dirección de correo electrónico, número de teléfono, contraseña"

msgctxt "biometric_data_collected"
msgid "Video and voice recordings"
msgstr "Grabaciones de vídeo y voz"

msgctxt "social_data_collected"
msgid "Neighbors app network"
msgstr "Red de la app Neighbors"

msgctxt "how_can_you_control_your_data"
msgid ""
"You may delete your recordings from Ring Protect at any time by accessing your account. In addition, to the extent required by applicable law, you may have the right to request access to or delete "
"your personal data (that is, if you are covered by CCPA or GDPR). No retention details are provided."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "how_can_you_control_your_data"
msgid ""
"In addition, law enforcement can make a video request in the Neighbors app to ask the community to assist in an investigation. Police who download videos from customer cameras may be able to keep "
"them indefinitely, <a id=\"a1\">depending on local laws.</a>"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "track_record_details"
msgid ""
"In <a id=\"a1\">November 2019,</a> a security vulnerability in Amazon's Ring Video Doorbell Pro devices could have allowed attackers to exploit the internet-connected doorbell to intercept the "
"owner's Wi-Fi credentials."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "track_record_details"
msgid "In 2019, <a id=\"a1\">Motherboard reported</a> on how Ring's weak security and compromised email addresses and passwords left Ring cameras easy to hack."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "track_record_details"
msgid "In <a id=\"a1\">December 2020</a>, a class action lawsuit was filed alleging lax security measures at Ring, allowed hackers to take over their devices."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "track_record_details"
msgid ""
"In <a id=\"a1\">August 2020</a>, security researchers from Check Point pointed out a flaw in Amazon's Alexa smart home devices that could have allowed hackers access to personal information and "
"conversation history. Amazon promptly fixed the bug."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "track_record_details"
msgid "In <a id=\"a1\">October 2020</a>, Amazon fired an employee for leaking customer email addresses to an unnamed third party."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "track_record_details"
msgid "In <a id=\"a1\">October 2019</a>, Forbes reported that Amazon employees were listening to Amazon Cloud Cam recording, to train its AI algorithm."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "track_record_details"
msgid ""
"In <a id=\"a1\">April 2019</a>, it was revealed that thousands of employees, many of whom are contract workers and some not even directly employed by Amazon, had access to both voice and text "
"transcripts of Alexa interactions."
msgstr ""

